radiographic_examinations.findings: Soft-tissue mass associated with the right carotid artery.

Large, intensely enhancing mass measuring 2.6 × 2.6 × 4.6 cm at the level of the right carotid bifurcation and a slightly smaller mass measuring 2.0 × 2.5 × 3.9 cm in the left side of the neck, consistent with bilateral carotid body tumors.
Nearly complete devascularization of the left carotid body tumor post-embolization.
Nearly complete devascularization with only a small residual inferior tumor not amenable to embolization in the right carotid body.
